  "texts": [
    "This is especially true for the more routine aspects of the review process, which require less intellectual input or domain expertise e.g., format and reproducibility checks, language/readability assessments, reviewer matching, and improving the writing of review reports.",
    "At the same time, there are important negative implications of using these tools in terms of biases, hallucinations, ethics, and other issues.",
    "Thus, editors and reviewers need to be cognizant of these challenges when employing AI to gain efficiencies in the review process.",
    "Going forward, more research is needed to mitigate these challenges and realize the full potential of AI augmentation and even automation for the peer review of IS research.",
